    "content": "# 物理引擎 v1.1\n\n物理引擎 v1.1 is the built-in guide for the `box2d` Scratch/Gandi extension.\nBox2D物理引擎，让两个小球同时落地。\n\nUse it for physics simulation, bodies, fixtures, joints, and collision events.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `box2d`.\n- DSL namespace: `box2d`. Full opcodes use the form `box2d_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-box2d\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setStage({ stageType: \"boxed\" });\nconst value = box2d.getVelocityX({  });\n```\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `box2d.setStage`\n\nBlock: `setStage`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `stageType`: text, menu `StageTypes`, default `boxed`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setStage({ stageType: \"boxed\" });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setGravity`\n\nBlock: `setGravity`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `gx`: number, default `0`.\n- `gy`: number, default `-10`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setGravity({ gx: 0, gy: -10 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setPhysics`\n\nBlock: `setPhysics`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `shape`: text, menu `ShapeTypes`, default `costume`.\n- `mode`: text, menu `EnableModeTypes`, default `normal`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setPhysics({ shape: \"costume\", mode: \"normal\" });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.disablePhysics`\n\nBlock: `disablePhysics`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.disablePhysics({  });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.doTick`\n\nBlock: `doTick`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.doTick({  });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setPosition`\n\nBlock: `setPosition`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `x`: number, default `0`.\n- `y`: number, default `0`.\n- `space`: text, menu `SpaceTypes`, default `world`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setPosition({ x: 0, y: 0, space: \"world\" });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setVelocity`\n\nBlock: `setVelocity`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `sx`: number, default `0`.\n- `sy`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setVelocity({ sx: 0, sy: 0 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.changeVelocity`\n\nBlock: `changeVelocity`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `sx`: number, default `0`.\n- `sy`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.changeVelocity({ sx: 0, sy: 0 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.getVelocityX`\n\nBlock: `getVelocityX`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.getVelocityX({  })\n```\n\n#### `box2d.getVelocityY`\n\nBlock: `getVelocityY`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.getVelocityY({  })\n```\n\n#### `box2d.applyForce`\n\nBlock: `applyForce`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `force`: number, default `25`.\n- `dir`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.applyForce({ force: 25, dir: 0 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.applyAngForce`\n\nBlock: `applyAngForce`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `force`: number, default `500`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.applyAngForce({ force: 500 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setStatic`\n\nBlock: `setStatic`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `static`: text, menu `StaticTypes`, default `static`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setStatic({ static: \"static\" });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setProperties`\n\nBlock: `setProperties`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `density`: number, menu `DensityTypes`, default `100`.\n- `friction`: number, menu `FrictionTypes`, default `50`.\n- `restitution`: number, menu `RestitutionTypes`, default `20`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setProperties({ density: 100, friction: 50, restitution: 20 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.getTouching`\n\nBlock: `getTouching`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `where`: text, menu `WhereTypes`, default `any`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.getTouching({ where: \"any\" })\n```\n\n#### `box2d.setScroll`\n\nBlock: `setScroll`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `ox`: number, default `0`.\n- `oy`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.setScroll({ ox: 0, oy: 0 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.changeScroll`\n\nBlock: `change scroll by x: [ox] y: [oy]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `ox`: number, default `0`.\n- `oy`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.changeScroll({ ox: 0, oy: 0 });\n```\n\n#### `box2d.getScrollX`\n\nBlock: `getScrollX`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.getScrollX({  })\n```\n\n#### `box2d.getScrollY`\n\nBlock: `getScrollY`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nbox2d.getScrollY({  })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `scratch3_box2d/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
