    "content": "# 连接 社区 v1.0\n\n连接 社区 v1.0 is the built-in guide for the `community` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n共创世界扩展语句及 APIs\n\nUse it for network requests, API calls, webhook callbacks, and remote data; structured data, object/list serialization, and parsing workflows; AI service calls, prompts, generated content, or model-driven project features.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `community`.\n- DSL namespace: `community`. Full opcodes use the form `community_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-community\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\ncommunity.postComment({ CONTENT: \"comment\", SCREENSHOT: \"false\" });\nconst value = community.isMyFans({  });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `userValues` (also accepts reporters): `communityExtensions.userID`, `communityExtensions.username`, `communityExtensions.userOid`, `communityExtensions.avatar`, `communityExtensions.constellation`, `communityExtensions.following`, `communityExtensions.followers`, `communityExtensions.liked`, `communityExtensions.gender`.\n- `USER_INFO_TYPE_MENU` (also accepts reporters): `communityExtensions.userID`, `communityExtensions.username`, `communityExtensions.userOid`, `communityExtensions.avatar`, `communityExtensions.constellation`, `communityExtensions.following`, `communityExtensions.followers`, `communityExtensions.liked`, `communityExtensions.gender`.\n- `SCREENSHOT_MENU`: `communityExtensions.screenshot.true`, `communityExtensions.screenshot.false`.\n- `STATS_MENU`: `communityExtensions.stats.comments`, `communityExtensions.stats.favorites`, `communityExtensions.stats.likes`, `communityExtensions.stats.coins`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Document and API Terms of Use\n\n#### `community.isMyFans`\n\nBlock: `is follower?`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.isMyFans({  })\n```\n\n#### `community.isFanOfSomeone`\n\nBlock: `is followed [WHO]?`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `WHO`: text, default `59fff36eefd0bf7679686631`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.isFanOfSomeone({ WHO: \"59fff36eefd0bf7679686631\" })\n```\n\n#### `community.getUserValue`\n\nBlock: `CCW USER VALUE [USERVALUE]`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `USERVALUE`: text, menu `USER_INFO_TYPE_MENU`, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.getUserValue({ USERVALUE: 1 })\n```\n\n#### `community.requestFollow`\n\nBlock: `request user to follow`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.requestFollow({  })\n```\n\n#### `community.isLiked`\n\nBlock: `liked this project?`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.isLiked({  })\n```\n\n#### `community.getCoinCount`\n\nBlock: `get inserted coins of this user`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.getCoinCount({  })\n```\n\n#### `community.insertCoinAndWaitForResult`\n\nBlock: `insert [COUNT] coins and wait for result`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `COUNT`: number, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.insertCoinAndWaitForResult({ COUNT: 1 })\n```\n\n#### `community.getProjectStatistics`\n\nBlock: `get project [STATS]`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `STATS`: text, menu `STATS_MENU`, default `comments`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.getProjectStatistics({ STATS: \"comments\" })\n```\n\n#### `community.postComment`\n\nBlock: `post comment [CONTENT], and [SCREENSHOT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `CONTENT`: text, default `comment`.\n- `SCREENSHOT`: text, menu `SCREENSHOT_MENU`, default `false`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.postComment({ CONTENT: \"comment\", SCREENSHOT: \"false\" });\n```\n\n#### `community.isUserLikedOtherProject`\n\nBlock: `is user liked project [PROJECT]?`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `PROJECT`: text, default `624d6e17a0c3b17a0b7a58ee`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.isUserLikedOtherProject({ PROJECT: \"624d6e17a0c3b17a0b7a58ee\" })\n```\n\n#### `community.isUserFavoriteOtherProject`\n\nBlock: `is user favorite project [PROJECT]?`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `PROJECT`: text, default `624d6e17a0c3b17a0b7a58ee`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.isUserFavoriteOtherProject({ PROJECT: \"624d6e17a0c3b17a0b7a58ee\" })\n```\n\n#### `community.redirect`\n\nBlock: `redirect to https://ccw.site/ [URL]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `URL`: text, default ` `.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.redirect({ URL: \" \" });\n```\n\n#### `community.genURLWithParams`\n\nBlock: `gen project link with data [DATA]`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `DATA`: text, default `data`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.genURLWithParams({ DATA: \"data\" })\n```\n\n#### `community.getURLParams`\n\nBlock: `get data from link`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.getURLParams({  })\n```\n\n#### `community.showShareUI`\n\nBlock: `show share view with[CODE] [DESC]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `CODE`: text, default `shareCode`.\n- `DESC`: text, default `description`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.showShareUI({ CODE: \"shareCode\", DESC: \"description\" });\n```\n\n#### `community.getShareCode`\n\nBlock: `get invite code from link`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.getShareCode({  })\n```\n\n#### `community.captureStageAsAvatar`\n\nBlock: `communityExtensions.captureStageAsAvatar`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ncommunity.captureStageAsAvatar({  });\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `scratch3_ccw_community/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
