    "content": "# 控制台\n\n控制台 is the built-in guide for the `Consoles` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n用于控制和操作浏览器内置的JavaScript控制台\n\nUse it for date, time, timer, calendar, and timezone logic.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `Consoles`.\n- DSL namespace: `Consoles`. Full opcodes use the form `Consoles_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-Consoles\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Emptying({  });\n```\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `Consoles.Emptying`\n\nBlock: `Emptying`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Emptying({  });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Information`\n\nBlock: `Information`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Information`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Information({ string: \"Information\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Journal`\n\nBlock: `Journal`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Journal`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Journal({ string: \"Journal\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Warning`\n\nBlock: `Warning`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Warning`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Warning({ string: \"Warning\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Error`\n\nBlock: `Error`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Error`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Error({ string: \"Error\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.debug`\n\nBlock: `debug`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `debug`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.debug({ string: \"debug\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.group`\n\nBlock: `group`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `group`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.group({ string: \"group\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.groupCollapsed`\n\nBlock: `groupCollapsed`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `group`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.groupCollapsed({ string: \"group\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.groupEnd`\n\nBlock: `groupEnd`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.groupEnd({  });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Timeron`\n\nBlock: `Timeron`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Time`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Timeron({ string: \"Time\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Timerlog`\n\nBlock: `Timerlog`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Time`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Timerlog({ string: \"Time\" });\n```\n\n#### `Consoles.Timeroff`\n\nBlock: `Timeroff`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `string`: text, default `Time`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nConsoles.Timeroff({ string: \"Time\" });\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `sipc.ink/ccw_sipc_console/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
