    "title": "移动端按键配置",
    "content": "# 移动端按键配置\n\n移动端按键配置 is the built-in guide for the `GandiJoystick` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n为你的游戏配置摇杆，让你的作品可以在手机、平板畅玩\n\nUse it for projects that need the extension-specific blocks listed below.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `GandiJoystick`.\n- DSL namespace: `GandiJoystick`. Full opcodes use the form `GandiJoystick_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-GandiJoystick\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.showMobileButtons({  });\nconst value = GandiJoystick.isDesignatedDeviceType({ DEVICE_TYPE: \"desktop\" });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `JOYSTICKS`: `GandiJoystick.leftJoystick`, `GandiJoystick.rightJoystick`.\n- `DEVICE_TYPES`: `GandiJoystick.desktop`, `GandiJoystick.tablet`, `GandiJoystick.mobile`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Customize mobile keyboard\n\n#### `GandiJoystick.isDesignatedDeviceType`\n\nBlock: `device type is [DEVICE_TYPE]`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `DEVICE_TYPE`: text, menu `DEVICE_TYPES`, default `desktop`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.isDesignatedDeviceType({ DEVICE_TYPE: \"desktop\" })\n```\n\n#### `GandiJoystick.showMobileButtons`\n\nBlock: `Display mobile buttons`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.showMobileButtons({  });\n```\n\n#### `GandiJoystick.hideMobileButtons`\n\nBlock: `Hide mobile buttons`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.hideMobileButtons({  });\n```\n\n#### `GandiJoystick.whenJoystickMoved`\n\nBlock: `when [JOYSTICK] is offset, and direction = [DIRECTION], offset distance = [DISTANCE]`\n\nType: hat.\n\nArguments:\n- `JOYSTICK`: text, menu `JOYSTICKS`, default `joystick-left`.\n- `direction`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n- `distance`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.whenJoystickMoved({ JOYSTICK: \"joystick-left\", direction: \"direction\", distance: \"distance\" }, () => {\n  // extension actions here\n});\n```\n\n#### `GandiJoystick.getJoystickDirection`\n\nBlock: `[JOYSTICK] direction`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `JOYSTICK`: text, menu `JOYSTICKS`, default `joystick-left`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.getJoystickDirection({ JOYSTICK: \"joystick-left\" })\n```\n\n#### `GandiJoystick.getJoystickDistance`\n\nBlock: `[JOYSTICK] offset distance`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `JOYSTICK`: text, menu `JOYSTICKS`, default `joystick-left`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiJoystick.getJoystickDistance({ JOYSTICK: \"joystick-left\" })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `gandi_joystick/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
