    "content": "# 控制台 v0.3.2\n\n控制台 v0.3.2 is the built-in guide for the `GandiTerminal` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n控制台可以输出运行中的变量，让 Debug 更方便。\n\nUse it for text formatting, parsing, string conversion, and display helpers.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `GandiTerminal`.\n- DSL namespace: `GandiTerminal`. Full opcodes use the form `GandiTerminal_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-GandiTerminal\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.showTerminal({ SHOW: \"1\" });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `SHOW_HIDE` (also accepts reporters): `GandiTerminal.show`, `GandiTerminal.hide`.\n- `COLOR_LIST`: `GandiTerminal.green`, `GandiTerminal.yellow`, `GandiTerminal.red`, `GandiTerminal.blue`, `GandiTerminal.magenta`, `GandiTerminal.cyan`, `GandiTerminal.white`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### How to use terminal\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.showTerminal`\n\nBlock: `[SHOW] terminal`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `SHOW`: text, menu `SHOW_HIDE`, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.showTerminal({ SHOW: \"1\" });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.log`\n\nBlock: `log [TEXT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `hello`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.log({ TEXT: \"hello\" });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.warn`\n\nBlock: `warn [TEXT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `warning`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.warn({ TEXT: \"warning\" });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.error`\n\nBlock: `error [TEXT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `error`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.error({ TEXT: \"error\" });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.trace`\n\nBlock: `trace [MARKER] : [TEXT] with color [COLOR]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `VALUE`.\n- `MARKER`: text, default `var`.\n- `COLOR`: text, menu `COLOR_LIST`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.trace({ TEXT: \"VALUE\", MARKER: \"var\", COLOR: \"<COLOR_LIST option>\" });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.traceWhenChanged`\n\nBlock: `trace [MARKER] : [TEXT] with color [COLOR] when VALUE changed`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `VALUE`.\n- `MARKER`: text, default `var`.\n- `COLOR`: text, menu `COLOR_LIST`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.traceWhenChanged({ TEXT: \"VALUE\", MARKER: \"var\", COLOR: \"<COLOR_LIST option>\" });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.clear`\n\nBlock: `clear`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.clear({  });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.dispatchEventFromTerminal`\n\nBlock: `when command received, [command]`\n\nType: hat.\n\nArguments:\n- `command`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.dispatchEventFromTerminal({ command: \"command\" }, () => {\n  // extension actions here\n});\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.pause`\n\nBlock: `pause`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.pause({  });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.continue`\n\nBlock: `continue`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.continue({  });\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.whenChanged`\n\nBlock: `when [VALUE] changed`\n\nType: hat.\n\nArguments:\n- `VALUE`: text, default `variable`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.whenChanged({ VALUE: \"variable\" }, () => {\n  // extension actions here\n});\n```\n\n#### `GandiTerminal.when`\n\nBlock: `when [A_BOOLEAN] turns true from false`\n\nType: hat.\n\nArguments:\n- `A_BOOLEAN`: Boolean, default ``.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nGandiTerminal.when({ A_BOOLEAN: \"\" }, () => {\n  // extension actions here\n});\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `gandi_ccw_terminal/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
