    "title": "图层管理 v1.01",
    "content": "# 图层管理 v1.01\n\n图层管理 v1.01 is the built-in guide for the `layerManager` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n图层排序不再是难题！\n\nUse it for off-stage drawing, image processing, custom rendering, and pixel workflows; sprite depth ordering and front/back layer management.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `layerManager`.\n- DSL namespace: `layerManager`. Full opcodes use the form `layerManager_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-layerManager\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setLayerManager({ OP: \"<ON_OR_OFF option>\" });\nconst value = layerManager.getTargetLayerInfo({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES_WITH_MY option>\", INFO: \"<LAYER_INFO option>\" });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `IF_ONLY_SPRITE`: `spritesAndClones`, `onlySprites`.\n- `SORTING_ORDER`: `descending`, `ascending`.\n- `ON_OR_OFF`: `activate`, `deactivate`.\n- `FOLDERS` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `LEVELS` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `SPRITES` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `SPRITES_WITH_MY` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `FRONT_OR_BEHIND`: `inFrontOf`, `behind`.\n- `AFFECTABLE`: `unaffected`, `affected`.\n- `LAYER_INFO`: `level`, `myPriority`, `myLayer`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `layerManager.setLayerManager`\n\nBlock: `setLayerManager`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `OP`: text, menu `ON_OR_OFF`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setLayerManager({ OP: \"<ON_OR_OFF option>\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setSortOrder`\n\nBlock: `setSortOrder`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `ORDER`: text, menu `SORTING_ORDER`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setSortOrder({ ORDER: \"<SORTING_ORDER option>\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.checkLayerLevelsButton`\n\nBlock: `checkLayerLevelsButton`\n\nType: palette button.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\n// Palette button: layerManager.checkLayerLevelsButton\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.defineLayerLevels`\n\nBlock: `defineLayerLevels`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `LEVELS`: text, default `defaultLevels`.\n- `LEVEL`: text, default `defaultLevel`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.defineLayerLevels({ LEVELS: \"defaultLevels\", LEVEL: \"defaultLevel\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.moveSpritesInFolderToLevel`\n\nBlock: `moveSpritesInFolderToLevel`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `FOLDER`: text, menu `FOLDERS`.\n- `LEVEL`: text, menu `LEVELS`, default `-`.\n- `TYPE`: text, menu `IF_ONLY_SPRITE`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.moveSpritesInFolderToLevel({ FOLDER: \"<FOLDERS option>\", LEVEL: \"-\", TYPE: \"<IF_ONLY_SPRITE option>\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setTargetLayerLevel`\n\nBlock: `setTargetLayerLevel`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET`: text, menu `SPRITES`.\n- `LEVEL`: text, menu `LEVELS`, default `-`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setTargetLayerLevel({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES option>\", LEVEL: \"-\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setTargetLayerPriority`\n\nBlock: `setTargetLayerPriority`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET`: text, menu `SPRITES_WITH_MY`.\n- `PRIORITY`: number, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setTargetLayerPriority({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES_WITH_MY option>\", PRIORITY: 1 });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.getTargetLayerInfo`\n\nBlock: `getTargetLayerInfo`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET`: text, menu `SPRITES_WITH_MY`.\n- `INFO`: text, menu `LAYER_INFO`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.getTargetLayerInfo({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES_WITH_MY option>\", INFO: \"<LAYER_INFO option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setCanvasLayerLevel`\n\nBlock: `setCanvasLayerLevel`\n\nType: command.\nHidden from the palette by default.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET`: text, menu `SPRITES_WITH_MY`.\n- `LEVEL`: text, menu `LEVELS`, default `-`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setCanvasLayerLevel({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES_WITH_MY option>\", LEVEL: \"-\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setCanvasLayerPriority`\n\nBlock: `setCanvasLayerPriority`\n\nType: command.\nHidden from the palette by default.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET`: text, menu `SPRITES_WITH_MY`.\n- `PRIORITY`: number, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setCanvasLayerPriority({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES_WITH_MY option>\", PRIORITY: 1 });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setMinUnshadedLevel`\n\nBlock: `setMinUnshadedLevel`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `LEVEL`: text, menu `LEVELS`, default `-`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setMinUnshadedLevel({ LEVEL: \"-\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setMinUnshadedIndex`\n\nBlock: `setMinUnshadedIndex`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `INDEX`: number, default `5`.\n- `LEVEL`: text, menu `LEVELS`, default `-`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setMinUnshadedIndex({ INDEX: 5, LEVEL: \"-\" });\n```\n\n#### `layerManager.setMinUnshadedTarget`\n\nBlock: `setMinUnshadedTarget`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET`: text, menu `SPRITES`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nlayerManager.setMinUnshadedTarget({ TARGET: \"<SPRITES option>\" });\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `gandi_arkos_layerManager/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
