    "content": "# 更多侦测\n\n更多侦测 is the built-in guide for the `moreSensing` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n提供云时间、更方便的按键检测等功能\n\nUse it for clone management, per-clone state, or targeting individual generated objects; file selection, local storage, archive, import, or export workflows; date, time, timer, calendar, and timezone logic.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `moreSensing`.\n- DSL namespace: `moreSensing`. Full opcodes use the form `moreSensing_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-moreSensing\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nconst value = moreSensing.getNetWorkTimeInfo({ TYPE: \"<NETWORK_TIME option>\" });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `FILE_LIST` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `TIME_UNITS` (also accepts reporters): `ms`, `s`, `min`, `h`, `d`, `m`, `y`.\n- `TIME_UNITS2` (also accepts reporters): `ms`, `s`, `min`, `h`, `d`, `m`, `y`, `hh:mm:ss`, `h min s`.\n- `NETWORK_TIME`: `tmstp`, `2000`, `delta`, `UTC`.\n- `DOWN_OR_UP`: `down`, `up`, `press`.\n- `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MYSELF` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MOUSE` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `SPRITE_MENU` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MOUSE_TAG` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `KEYBOARD` (also accepts reporters): dynamic menu.\n- `WOrH`: `0`, `1`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `moreSensing.getNetWorkTimeInfo`\n\nBlock: `getNetWorkTimeInfo`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TYPE`: text, menu `NETWORK_TIME`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.getNetWorkTimeInfo({ TYPE: \"<NETWORK_TIME option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.convertTime`\n\nBlock: `convertTime`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `VALUE`: number, default `60`.\n- `TYPE1`: text, menu `TIME_UNITS`, default `s`.\n- `TYPE2`: text, menu `TIME_UNITS2`, default `min`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.convertTime({ VALUE: 60, TYPE1: \"s\", TYPE2: \"min\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.isLogin`\n\nBlock: `isLogin`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.isLogin({  })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.getFile`\n\nBlock: `getFile`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `FILE`: text, menu `FILE_LIST`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.getFile({ FILE: \"<FILE_LIST option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.getComment`\n\nBlock: `getComment`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `CID`: text, menu `COMMENT_MENU`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.getComment({ CID: \"<COMMENT_MENU option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.cloneCount`\n\nBlock: `cloneCount`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.cloneCount({  })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.getStageInfo`\n\nBlock: `getStageInfo`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `INFO`: text, menu `WOrH`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.getStageInfo({ INFO: \"<WOrH option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.spritesList`\n\nBlock: `spritesList`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.spritesList({  })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.targetTouchingTarget`\n\nBlock: `targetTouchingTarget`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TARGET1`: text, menu `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MOUSE_TAG`.\n- `TARGET2`: text, menu `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.targetTouchingTarget({ TARGET1: \"<SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MOUSE_TAG option>\", TARGET2: \"<SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.touchingPoint`\n\nBlock: `touchingPoint`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `SPRITE`: text, menu `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG`.\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.touchingPoint({ SPRITE: \"<SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG option>\", X: 0, Y: 0 })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.touchingRect`\n\nBlock: `touchingRect`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `SPRITE`: text, menu `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MOUSE_TAG`.\n- `X1`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y1`: number, default `0`.\n- `X2`: number, default `100`.\n- `Y2`: number, default `100`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.touchingRect({ SPRITE: \"<SPRITE_MENU_WITH_MOUSE_TAG option>\", X1: 0, Y1: 0, X2: 100, Y2: 100 })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.pointInRect`\n\nBlock: `pointInRect`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `1`.\n- `Y`: number, default `1`.\n- `X1`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y1`: number, default `0`.\n- `X2`: number, default `100`.\n- `Y2`: number, default `100`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.pointInRect({ X: 1, Y: 1, X1: 0, Y1: 0, X2: 100, Y2: 100 })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.touchingLine`\n\nBlock: `touchingLine`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `SPRITE`: text, menu `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG`.\n- `X1`: number, default `-100`.\n- `Y1`: number, default `-100`.\n- `X2`: number, default `100`.\n- `Y2`: number, default `100`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.touchingLine({ SPRITE: \"<SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG option>\", X1: -100, Y1: -100, X2: 100, Y2: 100 })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.touchingRay`\n\nBlock: `touchingRay`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `SPRITE`: text, menu `SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG`.\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n- `DIS`: number, default `999`.\n- `DIR`: angle number, default `45`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.touchingRay({ SPRITE: \"<SPRITE_MENU_WITH_TAG option>\", X: 0, Y: 0, DIS: 999, DIR: 45 })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.amIOnTheTop`\n\nBlock: `amIOnTheTop`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.amIOnTheTop({ X: 0, Y: 0 })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.amIOnTheTopAtMouse`\n\nBlock: `amIOnTheTopAtMouse`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.amIOnTheTopAtMouse({  })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.amIclicked`\n\nBlock: `amIclicked`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.amIclicked({  })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.whenKeyDown`\n\nBlock: `whenKeyDown`\n\nType: Boolean reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `KEY`: text, menu `KEYBOARD`.\n- `TYPE`: text, menu `DOWN_OR_UP`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.whenKeyDown({ KEY: \"<KEYBOARD option>\", TYPE: \"<DOWN_OR_UP option>\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.colorToHex`\n\nBlock: `colorToHex`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `COLOR`: color.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.colorToHex({ COLOR: \"#ff0000\" })\n```\n\n#### `moreSensing.colorAt`\n\nBlock: `colorAt`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmoreSensing.colorAt({ X: 0, Y: 0 })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `arkos/moreSensing/moreSensing.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
