    "content": "# 音乐\n\n音乐 is the built-in guide for the `music` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n演奏乐器，敲锣打鼓。\n\nUse it for projects that need the extension-specific blocks listed below.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `music`.\n- DSL namespace: `music`. Full opcodes use the form `music_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-music\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_playDrumForBeats({ DRUM: 1, BEATS: 0.25 });\nconst value = music.music_getTempo({  });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `DRUM` (also accepts reporters): `(1) Snare Drum`, `(2) Bass Drum`, `(3) Side Stick`, `(4) Crash Cymbal`, `(5) Open Hi-Hat`, `(6) Closed Hi-Hat`, `(7) Tambourine`, `(8) Hand Clap`, `(9) Claves`, `(10) Wood Block`, `(11) Cowbell`, `(12) Triangle`, `(13) Bongo`, `(14) Conga`, `(15) Cabasa`, `(16) Guiro`.\n- `INSTRUMENT` (also accepts reporters): `(1) Piano`, `(2) Electric Piano`, `(3) Organ`, `(4) Guitar`, `(5) Electric Guitar`, `(6) Bass`, `(7) Pizzicato`, `(8) Cello`, `(9) Banjo`, `(10) Mandolin`, `(11) Trombone`, `(12) Clarinet`, `(13) Saxophone`, `(14) Trumpet`, `(15) Ring Organ`, `(16) Music Box`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `music.music_playDrumForBeats`\n\nBlock: `play drum [DRUM] for [BEATS] beats`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DRUM`: number, menu `DRUM`, default `1`.\n- `BEATS`: number, default `0.25`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_playDrumForBeats({ DRUM: 1, BEATS: 0.25 });\n```\n\n#### `music.music_restForBeats`\n\nBlock: `rest for [BEATS] beats`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `BEATS`: number, default `0.25`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_restForBeats({ BEATS: 0.25 });\n```\n\n#### `music.music_playNoteForBeats`\n\nBlock: `play note [NOTE] for [BEATS] beats`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `NOTE`: note, default `60`.\n- `BEATS`: number, default `0.25`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_playNoteForBeats({ NOTE: 60, BEATS: 0.25 });\n```\n\n#### `music.music_setInstrument`\n\nBlock: `set instrument to [INSTRUMENT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `INSTRUMENT`: number, menu `INSTRUMENT`, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_setInstrument({ INSTRUMENT: 1 });\n```\n\n#### `music.music_setTempo`\n\nBlock: `set tempo to [TEMPO]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEMPO`: number, default `60`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_setTempo({ TEMPO: 60 });\n```\n\n#### `music.music_changeTempo`\n\nBlock: `change tempo by [TEMPO]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEMPO`: number, default `20`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_changeTempo({ TEMPO: 20 });\n```\n\n#### `music.music_getTempo`\n\nBlock: `tempo`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nmusic.music_getTempo({  })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `../../../gandi-plugins`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n- Extraction note: `source_not_found`.\n"
