    "title": "角色特效 🚧",
    "content": "# 角色特效 🚧\n\n角色特效 🚧 is the built-in guide for the `spriteEffect` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n为角色添加更多特效\n\nUse it for projects that need the extension-specific blocks listed below.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `spriteEffect`.\n- DSL namespace: `spriteEffect`. Full opcodes use the form `spriteEffect_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-spriteEffect\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setNineSlice({ TOP: \"10\", LEFT: \"10\", RIGHT: \"10%\", BOTTOM: \"10%\", WIDTH: \"300%\", HEIGHT: \"200%\", MODE: \"stretch\" });\nconst value = spriteEffect.getScaleX({  });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `NINESLICE_RENDER_MODE`: `id`, `id`, `id`.\n- `EFFECT`: `id`, `id`, `id`, `id`, `id`, `id`.\n- `COSTUME_ATTRIBUTE`: `id`, `id`, `id`, `id`, `id`, `id`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `spriteEffect.setNineSlice`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TOP`: text, default `10`.\n- `LEFT`: text, default `10`.\n- `RIGHT`: text, default `10%`.\n- `BOTTOM`: text, default `10%`.\n- `WIDTH`: text, default `300%`.\n- `HEIGHT`: text, default `200%`.\n- `MODE`: text, menu `NINESLICE_RENDER_MODE`, default `stretch`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setNineSlice({ TOP: \"10\", LEFT: \"10\", RIGHT: \"10%\", BOTTOM: \"10%\", WIDTH: \"300%\", HEIGHT: \"200%\", MODE: \"stretch\" });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.setGaussianBlur`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setGaussianBlur({  });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.setTintColor`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `COLOR`: color, default `#00ff00`.\n- `AMOUNT`: number, default `30`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setTintColor({ COLOR: \"#00ff00\", AMOUNT: 30 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.setTile`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TH`: number, default `3`.\n- `TV`: number, default `2`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setTile({ TH: 3, TV: 2 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.clipRectange`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n- `WIDTH`: number, default `0.5`.\n- `HEIGHT`: number, default `0.5`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.clipRectange({ X: 0, Y: 0, WIDTH: 0.5, HEIGHT: 0.5 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.clipCircle`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n- `RADIUS`: number, default `0.5`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.clipCircle({ X: 0, Y: 0, RADIUS: 0.5 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.clipAngle`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `START`: number, default `0`.\n- `END`: number, default `90`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.clipAngle({ START: 0, END: 90 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.clearEffect`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `EFFECT`: text, menu `EFFECT`, default `<all>`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.clearEffect({ EFFECT: \"<all>\" });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.setScale`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `WIDTH`: number, default `100`.\n- `HEIGHT`: number, default `100`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setScale({ WIDTH: 100, HEIGHT: 100 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.getScaleX`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: reporter.\nHidden from the palette by default.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.getScaleX({  })\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.getScaleY`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: reporter.\nHidden from the palette by default.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.getScaleY({  })\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.setPivot`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `0`.\n- `Y`: number, default `0`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.setPivot({ X: 0, Y: 0 });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.resetPivot`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.resetPivot({  });\n```\n\n#### `spriteEffect.costumeAttribute`\n\nBlock: `id`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `ATTRIBUTE`: text, menu `COSTUME_ATTRIBUTE`, default `scaleX`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nspriteEffect.costumeAttribute({ ATTRIBUTE: \"scaleX\" })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `gandi_ccw_spriteEffect/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
