    "content": "# 特洛无人机\n\n特洛无人机 is the built-in guide for the `tello` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n操控无人机的神奇代码。\n\nUse it for projects that need the extension-specific blocks listed below.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `tello`.\n- DSL namespace: `tello`. Full opcodes use the form `tello_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-tello\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\ntello.takeoff({  });\nconst value = tello.battery({  });\n```\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `tello.takeoff`\n\nBlock: `takeoff`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.takeoff({  });\n```\n\n#### `tello.land`\n\nBlock: `land`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.land({  });\n```\n\n#### `tello.up`\n\nBlock: `fly up [DISTANCE] cm`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.up({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.down`\n\nBlock: `fly down [DISTANCE] cm`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.down({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.left`\n\nBlock: `fly left [DISTANCE] cm`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.left({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.right`\n\nBlock: `fly right [DISTANCE] cm`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.right({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.forward`\n\nBlock: `fly forward [DISTANCE] cm`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.forward({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.back`\n\nBlock: `fly backward [DISTANCE] cm`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.back({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.clockwise`\n\nBlock: `rotate [DISTANCE] degree clockwise`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `90`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.clockwise({ DISTANCE: 90 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.anticlockwise`\n\nBlock: `rotate [DISTANCE] degree counter clockwise`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `90`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.anticlockwise({ DISTANCE: 90 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.speed`\n\nBlock: `set speed to [DISTANCE] cm/s`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: number, default `50`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.speed({ DISTANCE: 50 });\n```\n\n#### `tello.flip`\n\nBlock: `filp [DISTANCE]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `DISTANCE`: text, menu `flipMenu`, default `f`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.flip({ DISTANCE: \"f\" });\n```\n\n#### `tello.emergency`\n\nBlock: `emergency stop`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.emergency({  });\n```\n\n#### `tello.stop`\n\nBlock: `stop and hover`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.stop({  });\n```\n\n#### `tello.toggleVideo`\n\nBlock: `turn video [TOGGLE]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TOGGLE`: text, menu `toggleVideoMenu`, default `streamon`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.toggleVideo({ TOGGLE: \"streamon\" });\n```\n\n#### `tello.screenshot`\n\nBlock: `photoshot`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.screenshot({  });\n```\n\n#### `tello.go`\n\nBlock: `fly to MissionPad x[X]cm  y[Y]cm  z[Z]cm with speed [SPEED]cm/s Mid[MID]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `X`: number, default `50`.\n- `Y`: number, default `50`.\n- `Z`: number, default `50`.\n- `SPEED`: number, default `50`.\n- `MID`: text, menu `telloChallengeCardMenu`, default `m1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.go({ X: 50, Y: 50, Z: 50, SPEED: 50, MID: \"m1\" });\n```\n\n#### `tello.battery`\n\nBlock: `battery(%)`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.battery({  })\n```\n\n#### `tello.tofHeight`\n\nBlock: `tof distance(cm)`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.tofHeight({  })\n```\n\n#### `tello.mid`\n\nBlock: `挑战卡编号`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntello.mid({  })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `scratch3_xigua_tello/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
