    "title": "艺术字 v2.0.4",
    "content": "# 艺术字 v2.0.4\n\n艺术字 v2.0.4 is the built-in guide for the `text` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n有渐变，能换行，让文字变得栩栩如生。\n\nUse it for text formatting, parsing, string conversion, and display helpers.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `text`.\n- DSL namespace: `text`. Full opcodes use the form `text_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-text\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\ntext.setText({ TEXT: \"DefaultText\" });\nconst value = text.calculateText({ TEXT: \"text.DefaultAnimateText\", PROP: \"lines\" });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `SPEED`: `text.speed.1x`, `text.speed.1_5x`, `text.speed.2x`, `text.speed.3x`, `text.speed.5x`, `text.speed.10x`, `text.speed.inf`, `text.speed.pause`.\n- `PROP`: `text.prop.lines`, `text.prop.width`, `text.prop.height`.\n- `FONT`: `text.font.randomFont`.\n- `ALIGN`: `text.align.left`, `text.align.center`, `text.align.right`, `text.align.abs_left`, `text.align.abs_right`.\n- `DIRECTION`: `text.setColorGradient.updown`, `text.setColorGradient.leftright`.\n- `WRAP_MODE`: `text.wrapMode.width`, `text.wrapMode.symbol`.\n- `ANIMATE`: `text.animate.type`, `text.animate.rainbow`, `text.animate.zoom`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Document\n\n#### `text.setText`\n\nBlock: `show text [TEXT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `DefaultText`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setText({ TEXT: \"DefaultText\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.animateText`\n\nBlock: `[ANIMATE] text [TEXT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `ANIMATE`: text, menu `ANIMATE`, default `rainbow`.\n- `TEXT`: text, default `text.DefaultAnimateText`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.animateText({ ANIMATE: \"rainbow\", TEXT: \"text.DefaultAnimateText\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.clearText`\n\nBlock: `show sprite`\n\nType: command.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.clearText({  });\n```\n\n#### `text.setFont`\n\nBlock: `set font to [FONT]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `FONT`: text, menu `FONT`, default `fzdlt`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setFont({ FONT: \"fzdlt\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.setColor`\n\nBlock: `set text color to [COLOR]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `COLOR`: color.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setColor({ COLOR: \"#ff0000\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.setWidth`\n\nBlock: `set width to [WIDTH] aligned [ALIGN]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `WIDTH`: number, default `200`.\n- `ALIGN`: text, menu `ALIGN`, default `left`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setWidth({ WIDTH: 200, ALIGN: \"left\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.dispatchFontLoaded`\n\nBlock: `when font [font] loaded`\n\nType: hat.\n\nArguments:\n- `font`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.dispatchFontLoaded({ font: \"font\" }, () => {\n  // extension actions here\n});\n```\n\n#### `text.setLineBreakMode`\n\nBlock: `wrap line by [MODE]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `MODE`: text, menu `WRAP_MODE`, default `width`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setLineBreakMode({ MODE: \"width\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.setLineHeight`\n\nBlock: `wrap line height: [H]x`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `H`: number, default `1.25`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setLineHeight({ H: 1.25 });\n```\n\n#### `text.setColorGradient`\n\nBlock: `set color gradient from [COLOR] to [COLOR2] with [DIRECTION]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `COLOR`: color, default `#8aec80`.\n- `COLOR2`: color, default `#5FC454`.\n- `DIRECTION`: text, menu `DIRECTION`, default `updown`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setColorGradient({ COLOR: \"#8aec80\", COLOR2: \"#5FC454\", DIRECTION: \"updown\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.setStroke`\n\nBlock: `set stroke [WIDTH] color [COLOR]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `WIDTH`: number, default `1`.\n- `COLOR`: color, default `#000000`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setStroke({ WIDTH: 1, COLOR: \"#000000\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.calculateText`\n\nBlock: `calculate [PROP] [TEXT]`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TEXT`: text, default `text.DefaultAnimateText`.\n- `PROP`: text, menu `PROP`, default `lines`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.calculateText({ TEXT: \"text.DefaultAnimateText\", PROP: \"lines\" })\n```\n\n#### `text.animateTextAdv`\n\nBlock: `type text [TEXT], every [TICK] ms a letter`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `TICK`: number, default `60`.\n- `TEXT`: text, default `text.DefaultAnimateText`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.animateTextAdv({ TICK: 60, TEXT: \"text.DefaultAnimateText\" });\n```\n\n#### `text.setAnimationSpeed`\n\nBlock: `set type speed to [SPEED]`\n\nType: command.\n\nArguments:\n- `SPEED`: number, menu `SPEED`, default `1`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.setAnimationSpeed({ SPEED: 1 });\n```\n\n#### `text.dispatchTextTyped`\n\nBlock: `when [character] typed, typed:[typedString], rest:[restString]`\n\nType: hat.\n\nArguments:\n- `character`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n- `typedString`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n- `restString`: ccw_hat_parameter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\ntext.dispatchTextTyped({ character: \"character\", typedString: \"typedstring\", restString: \"reststring\" }, () => {\n  // extension actions here\n});\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `scratch3_text/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
