    "content": "# 时间计算 v1.1\n\n时间计算 v1.1 is the built-in guide for the `VIDateTime` Scratch/Gandi extension.\n计算日期与时间\n\nUse it for date, time, timer, calendar, and timezone logic.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- Extension ID: `VIDateTime`.\n- DSL namespace: `VIDateTime`. Full opcodes use the form `VIDateTime_<opcode>`.\n- Use `getAllExtensions` or `getExtensionBlocks` when you need the live block list from the current project.\n- Use `getBlocksHelp` for any opcode before writing unfamiliar DSL, especially when menus or reporter inputs are involved.\n- Patch `/<target>/scripts/*.js` feature files. A file may contain multiple `// @script <id>` sections; each section must have exactly one top-level hat or stack.\n- Menu inputs should use the menu values listed in this guide or the live values returned by `getBlocksHelp`.\n\n## Recommended Flow\n\n1. Add the extension to the project if it is not already loaded.\n2. Read this guide with `getScratchGuide({ topic: \"extension-VIDateTime\" })`.\n3. Use `getExtensionBlocks` or `getBlocksHelp` for the exact opcode and argument names you will patch.\n4. Write DSL with the namespace and opcode names below.\n5. Run `getDiagnostics` after patching scripts that use this extension.\n\nExample DSL shape:\n\n```js\nconst value = VIDateTime.date({ YEAR: 1, MONTH: \"1\", DATE: 1 });\n```\n\n## Common Menu Values\n\n- `DiffUnits`: `VIDateTime.get.days`, `VIDateTime.get.hour`, `VIDateTime.get.minute`, `VIDateTime.get.second`, `VIDateTime.get.millisecond`.\n- `Units`: `VIDateTime.get.year`, `VIDateTime.get.month`, `VIDateTime.get.date`, `VIDateTime.get.day`, `VIDateTime.get.hour`, `VIDateTime.get.minute`, `VIDateTime.get.second`, `VIDateTime.get.millisecond`.\n\n## Blocks\n\n### Blocks\n\n#### `VIDateTime.date`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.date`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `YEAR`: number.\n- `MONTH`: number, default `1`.\n- `DATE`: number.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.date({ YEAR: 1, MONTH: \"1\", DATE: 1 })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.time`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.time`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `YEAR`: number.\n- `MONTH`: number, default `1`.\n- `DATE`: number.\n- `HOUR`: number.\n- `MINUTE`: number.\n- `SECOND`: number.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.time({ YEAR: 1, MONTH: \"1\", DATE: 1, HOUR: 1, MINUTE: 1, SECOND: 1 })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.now`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.now`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.now({  })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.today`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.today`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.today({  })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.after2000`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.after2000`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `DAYS`: number.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.after2000({ DAYS: 1 })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.diff2000`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.diff2000`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TIME`: text.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.diff2000({ TIME: \"time\" })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.diff`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.diff`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TIME1`: text, default `2000-01-23T12:34:56`.\n- `TIME2`: text.\n- `UNIT`: text, menu `DiffUnits`, default `days`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.diff({ TIME1: \"2000-01-23T12:34:56\", TIME2: \"time2\", UNIT: \"days\" })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.add`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.add`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TIME1`: text, default `2000-01-23T12:34:56`.\n- `TIME2`: number, default `1234`.\n- `UNIT`: text, menu `DiffUnits`, default `days`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.add({ TIME1: \"2000-01-23T12:34:56\", TIME2: 1234, UNIT: \"days\" })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.get`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.get`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nArguments:\n- `TIME`: text.\n- `UNIT`: text, menu `Units`, default `date`.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.get({ TIME: \"time\", UNIT: \"date\" })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.timezone`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.timezone`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.timezone({  })\n```\n\n#### `VIDateTime.timezonemin`\n\nBlock: `VIDateTime.timezonemin`\n\nType: reporter.\n\nDSL:\n\n```js\nVIDateTime.timezonemin({  })\n```\n\n## Pitfalls\n\n- Do not guess argument names from the visible block text; use the argument names shown above or from `getBlocksHelp`.\n- Menus may be localized in the UI. DSL usually needs the underlying menu value, not necessarily the translated label.\n- Reporter blocks can be nested inside other extension/core inputs; command blocks must be placed in a stack.\n- If a block has no static metadata here, inspect the current runtime because some extensions build blocks dynamically.\n- After changing scripts, run diagnostics and fix any unexpected input or menu errors before continuing.\n\n## Source\n\n- Extension source: `gandi_community_time/index.js`.\n- Generated from `D:/projects/scratch-extensions/src/extensions`.\n"
